  "summaryEn": "The firm Circle, responsible for the stablecoin USDC, is facing severe criticism after funds stolen during a hack at derivatives platform Drift were not frozen. Analysts highlight the potential impact on trust and credibility in stablecoins.",
  "contentEn": "<p>The firm Circle, known as the primary issuer of the stablecoin USDC, is under intense scrutiny following reports that funds stolen during a hack on the derivatives platform Drift were not frozen. According to CoinDesk, this inaction has led to severe criticism and concerns about risk management practices in cryptocurrency platforms.</p>\n\n<h2>Impact on Trust</h2>\n<p>The incident has raised key questions about how funds are handled and integrity is ensured for stablecoins. Analysts quoted by CoinGlass point out that such events can rapidly erode trust within the crypto ecosystem.</p>\n\n<h2>Hack Details</h2>\n<p>The hack occurred recently when approximately 35 million USDC were stolen during an attack on Drift. Instead of freezing these funds, Circle did not take immediate action to recover them or protect affected users.</p>\n\n<h2>Trust and Credibility</h2>\n<p>\"The lack of action by Circle has generated significant concern in the crypto community,\" mentioned a representative from CoinGlass. \"Such events can have a substantial impact on trust and credibility within the ecosystem.\"</p>\n\n<h2>Market Context</h2>\n<p>While this event garners attention, the cryptocurrency market continues to show moderate fluctuations. According to CoinGecko, Bitcoin (BTC) is trading at $66,831 with a 0.72% change in the last 24 hours. Ethereum (ETH) stands at $2,048.94, experiencing a weekly variation of 0.25%. Tether (USDT), Ripple (XRP), and BNB also show stable levels.</p>\n\n<h2>Impact on USDC</h2>\n<p>The value of USDC has shown some volatility following the incident but still maintains parity with the U.S. dollar. This is crucial for maintaining market confidence in the stability and solvency of stablecoins.</p>\n\n<h2>Regulations and Compliance</h2>\n<p>The case also highlights the importance of regulatory compliance within the cryptocurrency ecosystem. The lack of clear rules and effective implementation can lead to critical situations like this one.</p>\n\n<h2>Institutional Support</h2>\n<p>Amidst scrutiny, some investment firms have shown support for the crypto ecosystem. For example, Standard Chartered has forecasted that Bitcoin (BTC) could reach $500,000 by 2030.</p>\n\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>In spite of these challenges, the cryptocurrency market continues to demonstrate resilience. The incident involving Circle and Drift serves as a call for action to improve security practices and compliance across all platforms.</p>"
